WEBVTT

1
00:01:07.875 --> 00:01:10.125
<i>No one told me</i>
<i>that love could hurt so much.</i>

2
00:01:10.958 --> 00:01:12.375
<i>That it was like a rose.</i>

3
00:01:13.375 --> 00:01:16.666
<i>If you endure the thorns.</i>
<i>you get to the flower.</i>

4
00:01:18.833 --> 00:01:22.750
BASED ON THE WATTPAD NOVEL BOULEVARD
WRITTEN BY FLOR M. SALVADOR

5
00:01:44.250 --> 00:01:45.666
{\an8}<i>Good morning.</i>

6
00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:50.416
{\an8}<i>Today is your first day of high school.</i>
<i>I hope you have a great day. sweetie.</i>

7
00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:53.125
{\an8}<i>I'm sure you'll love it</i>
<i>and make tons of new friends.</i>

8
00:01:53.708 --> 00:01:57.291
{\an8}<i>I'm already at the hospital.</i>
<i>so. wish me luck. okay?</i>

9
00:01:57.375 --> 00:01:59.416
{\an8}<i>Kisses. sweetie. Mwah. I love you.</i>

10
00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.458
Sorry. where's the classroom
for second year?

11
00:02:17.541 --> 00:02:19.208
-That door over there.
-Thanks.

12
00:02:21.500 --> 00:02:22.791
Sorry. I'm late.

13
00:02:23.583 --> 00:02:24.625
And you are?

14
00:02:33.166 --> 00:02:34.250
Idiot.

15
00:02:50.625 --> 00:02:53.291
-One of the most brilliant periods of our…
-Hi.

16
00:02:56.125 --> 00:02:57.833
Sorry. I'm new here and…

17
00:02:57.916 --> 00:02:59.083
You're late.

18
00:03:02.875 --> 00:03:05.250
Hasley… Weigel?

19
00:03:05.958 --> 00:03:06.791
Weigel.

20
00:03:08.083 --> 00:03:10.083
-My dad's German.
-Okay.

21
00:03:13.291 --> 00:03:14.166
Sir…

22
00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:16.375
Latecomers aren't allowed in my class.

23
00:03:18.250 --> 00:03:19.166
Seriously?

24
00:03:26.291 --> 00:03:29.833
As I was saying.
this year we'll begin with the Golden Age.

25
00:03:48.291 --> 00:03:49.416
You're a jerk.

26
00:03:50.833 --> 00:03:53.166
-They kicked me out.
-Technically. they didn't.

27
00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:56.250
Because they would've had
to let you in first.

28
00:03:59.750 --> 00:04:02.166
And why are you sitting here
smoking joints?

29
00:04:02.250 --> 00:04:03.583
Trying to look cool?

30
00:04:06.333 --> 00:04:08.166
-Want some?
-Gross.

31
00:04:11.083 --> 00:04:11.916
What's that?

32
00:04:13.791 --> 00:04:14.708
Shit.

33
00:04:18.291 --> 00:04:20.125
It's toothpaste. okay?

34
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:22.958
You're funny…

35
00:04:25.125 --> 00:04:25.958
Hasley.

36
00:04:26.958 --> 00:04:29.708
Weigel. Hasley Weigel.
My dad's German. Happy?

37
00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:33.583
"Hasley Weigel."

38
00:04:33.666 --> 00:04:35.125
Just Hasley.

39
00:04:42.958 --> 00:04:43.916
What's your name?

40
00:04:49.875 --> 00:04:50.791
Hasley.

41
00:04:53.583 --> 00:04:55.000
-You're Hasley. right?
-Yeah.

42
00:04:55.083 --> 00:04:56.666
Cool. I'm Olivia. Call me Oli.

43
00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:58.333
-From class?
-Yeah.

44
00:04:58.416 --> 00:05:00.250
Listen. that really sucked earlier.

45
00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:03.750
Don't worry. he's the worst of them all.
The rest aren't so bad.

46
00:05:03.833 --> 00:05:06.291
-Just a little bit.
-Just a little bit.

47
00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.666
We're outside on the stairs
having something to drink.

48
00:05:09.750 --> 00:05:12.000
Would you like to join us?

49
00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:13.708
-Can I?
-Yeah.

50
00:05:14.541 --> 00:05:16.166
Okay. I'll grab something first.

51
00:05:16.250 --> 00:05:17.625
Great. See you in a bit.

52
00:05:21.375 --> 00:05:22.375
Hasley.

53
00:05:23.875 --> 00:05:28.333
Okay. people. I'll do the introductions.
This is Hasley.

54
00:05:28.833 --> 00:05:30.208
-That's Dylan.
-Hey.

55
00:05:30.291 --> 00:05:31.541
-Zev.
-Hello.

56
00:05:31.625 --> 00:05:33.208
Neizan and Carla.

57
00:05:33.291 --> 00:05:34.541
-Hi.
-Hi.

58
00:05:35.916 --> 00:05:36.833
How's it going?

59
00:05:38.333 --> 00:05:40.291
Hey. Oli. who's that blond guy?

60
00:05:41.875 --> 00:05:42.875
Him?

61
00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:44.791
That's Luke Howland.

62
00:05:44.875 --> 00:05:47.291
He's a loser.
You'd better stay away from him.

63
00:05:47.375 --> 00:05:49.333
-Why?
-He's not right in the head.

64
00:05:49.416 --> 00:05:51.291
He's a weirdo who loses his temper.

65
00:05:51.375 --> 00:05:52.625
-You guys are mean.
-What?

66
00:05:56.708 --> 00:06:00.250
-What are you guys talking about?
-Hey. about the <i>junkie.</i>

67
00:06:00.333 --> 00:06:01.583
-Ah. Luke.
-Super.

68
00:06:03.541 --> 00:06:05.291
Hi. I'm Matt.

69
00:06:06.916 --> 00:06:08.041
Nice to meet you.

70
00:06:08.750 --> 00:06:09.666
Hasley.

71
00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:10.666
Hasley?

72
00:06:11.583 --> 00:06:14.000
What a pretty name. You're new. right?

73
00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:16.875
You still have time to run away.

74
00:06:16.958 --> 00:06:17.833
Ignore him.

75
00:06:19.583 --> 00:06:23.166
That's going to be difficult.
My mom is the new psychologist.

76
00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:24.583
-At school?
-Shit.

77
00:06:24.666 --> 00:06:26.291
And at the hospital too.

78
00:06:26.375 --> 00:06:27.833
Your mom's the school shrink?

79
00:06:27.916 --> 00:06:29.791
Why would you say that? Are you dumb?

80
00:06:29.875 --> 00:06:32.791
-Sorry. Don't be such a thin-skinned wimp.
-What did you say?

81
00:06:32.875 --> 00:06:34.916
They're nice. I promise.

82
00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:37.791
If they bother you. call me.
And if they don't. call me anyway.

83
00:06:39.416 --> 00:06:41.458
Time to go back to the cage.

84
00:06:41.541 --> 00:06:44.041
We have practice this weekend.
Are you guys coming?

85
00:06:44.125 --> 00:06:45.708
Yeah. sure.

86
00:06:45.791 --> 00:06:48.375
And you can come too
so we can catch you up on everything.

87
00:06:48.458 --> 00:06:49.416
Yeah. okay.

88
00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:50.833
Don't let me down. Hasley.

89
00:06:51.625 --> 00:06:53.041
Okay. Romeo.

90
00:06:54.291 --> 00:06:55.208
See you later.

91
00:06:55.291 --> 00:06:57.375
What do you think? Cool. right?

92
00:07:00.708 --> 00:07:03.083
So. what's wrong with this Luke guy?

93
00:07:03.166 --> 00:07:06.000
-Everything's wrong with him.
-Since his brother killed himself.

94
00:07:06.083 --> 00:07:08.375
-He's crazy. Always causing trouble.
-Come on. Carla.

95
00:07:08.458 --> 00:07:11.208
What? She should know
so she doesn't go near him. right?

96
00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:31.458
Sweetie.
if you're thinking of running away.

97
00:07:31.541 --> 00:07:34.125
write me a note
without spelling mistakes. please.

98
00:07:36.541 --> 00:07:37.583
Good night.

99
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:40.000
I love you.

100
00:07:46.625 --> 00:07:47.708
Shit.

101
00:07:49.041 --> 00:07:52.500
…thirty-five in Seville
at the Palacio de Dueñas.

102
00:07:52.583 --> 00:07:56.791
which was rented out
to several families living there.

103
00:07:56.875 --> 00:07:58.250
When he was eight…

104
00:08:02.166 --> 00:08:05.125
DREAMS

105
00:08:07.375 --> 00:08:08.500
Weigel.

106
00:08:10.583 --> 00:08:12.541
Shouldn't you be in class?

107
00:08:15.083 --> 00:08:17.375
You're correct. Luke Howland.

108
00:08:19.708 --> 00:08:21.000
I didn't feel like going.

109
00:08:22.666 --> 00:08:24.291
So you know my name.

110
00:08:31.708 --> 00:08:33.125
Getting high so early?

111
00:08:35.333 --> 00:08:36.583
It relieves my stress.

112
00:08:51.541 --> 00:08:52.833
"Sleep under the stars."

113
00:08:53.708 --> 00:08:54.791
"Travel to Paris."

114
00:08:55.916 --> 00:08:58.166
"Make a trip in a hippie van…"

115
00:08:58.250 --> 00:08:59.166
Hey.

116
00:08:59.250 --> 00:09:01.083
"Plant a tree."

117
00:09:01.833 --> 00:09:04.500
"Dance in public
without caring about anything."

118
00:09:04.583 --> 00:09:06.041
"Light fireworks."

119
00:09:06.125 --> 00:09:08.958
Enough. That's private.

120
00:09:09.791 --> 00:09:12.333
What is it? A bucket list or something?

121
00:09:13.375 --> 00:09:14.208
You're dying.

122
00:09:16.958 --> 00:09:18.333
They're dreams.

123
00:09:18.416 --> 00:09:19.541
A bit weird. though.

124
00:09:20.833 --> 00:09:23.916
It's clear you've never had to live
constantly on the move.

125
00:09:25.916 --> 00:09:27.750
Well. just so you know. I envy you.

126
00:09:27.833 --> 00:09:29.208
Having dreams and stuff.

127
00:09:29.958 --> 00:09:31.416
That's not for me.

128
00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:33.916
After all.
dreams are shattered in the end.

129
00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:36.041
No. I disagree.

130
00:09:36.125 --> 00:09:39.041
They give me hope. Like…

131
00:09:40.250 --> 00:09:42.666
Like there's something else to live for.

132
00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:47.833
In other words. made-up goals
to give meaning to a shitty life. right?

133
00:09:48.416 --> 00:09:50.500
What's the point of living a life
based on lies?

134
00:09:51.541 --> 00:09:54.250
They're only lies
if you don't fulfill them.

135
00:09:54.333 --> 00:09:56.500
And simmer down. you must have dreams too.

136
00:09:58.166 --> 00:10:02.166
Well. right now
I'm thinking of having a pot brownie

137
00:10:02.250 --> 00:10:04.000
to get me through the morning.

138
00:10:04.083 --> 00:10:06.791
-Sure. that's all you think about. right?
-No.

139
00:10:07.958 --> 00:10:10.333
I also think about
swimming with dolphins. for example.

140
00:10:11.750 --> 00:10:15.083
Jumping off a cliff.
Driving with no destination.

141
00:10:16.583 --> 00:10:19.291
And traveling to Amsterdam. That too.

142
00:10:19.375 --> 00:10:20.541
To eat brownies. right?

143
00:10:22.083 --> 00:10:23.000
Right.

144
00:10:30.666 --> 00:10:34.291
Hey. is that the dispersion of light
on your T-shirt?

145
00:10:35.041 --> 00:10:36.083
You're joking.

146
00:10:36.666 --> 00:10:38.375
You don't know Pink Floyd?

147
00:10:39.416 --> 00:10:41.041
Yeah. that name rings a bell.

148
00:10:41.125 --> 00:10:44.375
How could it not? It's one of the best
rock bands in history.

149
00:10:45.166 --> 00:10:46.208
Radiohead.

150
00:10:46.916 --> 00:10:48.916
The Offspring. The Doors.

151
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:52.625
I mean. I'm sure I've listened to them
at some point.

152
00:10:52.708 --> 00:10:53.666
Not even Green Day?

153
00:10:53.750 --> 00:10:57.291
Okay. enough. Spare my life.
I'll just get my phone out and…

154
00:10:57.375 --> 00:10:59.291
What? No. stop.

155
00:10:59.375 --> 00:11:01.541
If it's your first time.
you have to do it right.

156
00:11:02.333 --> 00:11:03.500
And how do you do that?

157
00:11:04.083 --> 00:11:05.125
On vinyl.

158
00:11:05.916 --> 00:11:07.500
How old are you. 80?

159
00:11:09.083 --> 00:11:12.166
You clearly need me to show you
how great music was born.

160
00:11:12.250 --> 00:11:13.208
You're a freak.

161
00:11:17.875 --> 00:11:21.708
Want a toke?
Sometimes it's good to break the rules.

162
00:11:21.791 --> 00:11:23.916
I will not put that joint in my mouth.

163
00:11:24.666 --> 00:11:26.916
Hey. you two. What are you doing?
Stand up.

164
00:11:31.125 --> 00:11:32.500
To the principal's office. now.

165
00:11:32.583 --> 00:11:33.625
-It's mine.
-I said now.

166
00:11:33.708 --> 00:11:34.833
I don't even know her.

167
00:11:35.625 --> 00:11:38.083
You. go to the principal's office.
And you. go to class.

168
00:11:49.458 --> 00:11:53.041
Well. I skipped class
almost involuntarily.

169
00:11:54.208 --> 00:11:55.666
I mean it. I was late again.

170
00:11:55.750 --> 00:11:59.208
and since that guy wasn't going
to let me in. well. that was that.

171
00:11:59.291 --> 00:12:04.083
Yeah. "almost" involuntary.
You've got some nerve.

172
00:12:04.166 --> 00:12:07.208
Don't worry. okay?
You'll get used to the schedule.

173
00:12:10.791 --> 00:12:12.958
Hasley. are you doing anything later?

174
00:12:13.916 --> 00:12:14.750
No. why?

175
00:12:14.833 --> 00:12:16.583
Want to grab a drink?

176
00:12:17.833 --> 00:12:19.416
Yeah. sure.

177
00:12:20.541 --> 00:12:22.958
Perfect. See you later. then.

178
00:12:23.041 --> 00:12:24.375
Okay. take your seats.

179
00:12:24.958 --> 00:12:28.500
Matt. what are you doing here?
Get back to your class. you're late.

180
00:12:29.875 --> 00:12:31.000
For a good reason.

181
00:12:47.458 --> 00:12:49.791
How are you doing
with the move and everything?

182
00:12:50.375 --> 00:12:54.500
Well. I don't usually
get around to unpacking the boxes.

183
00:12:54.583 --> 00:12:55.666
How come?

184
00:12:55.750 --> 00:12:58.458
We're usually on the move again
before I can get to it.

185
00:12:58.958 --> 00:13:03.291
I've lived here all my life.
but I travel with the team.

186
00:13:04.416 --> 00:13:05.250
Basketball. right?

187
00:13:05.333 --> 00:13:07.500
The team captain. no less.

188
00:13:10.208 --> 00:13:13.166
And what's life like here?

189
00:13:14.041 --> 00:13:18.041
Well. you know.
life can be hell in a small town.

190
00:13:19.458 --> 00:13:22.083
Don't worry.
I'll make sure it's paradise for you.

191
00:13:22.166 --> 00:13:23.833
I'm very flattered.

192
00:13:27.041 --> 00:13:28.041
To new beginnings.

193
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:32.875
Thanks for walking me home.

194
00:13:32.958 --> 00:13:35.791
My pleasure. That way I got to spend
a little more time with you.

195
00:13:37.375 --> 00:13:38.291
We're here.

196
00:13:44.416 --> 00:13:45.875
I had a good time today. Has.

197
00:13:47.458 --> 00:13:48.375
Me too.

198
00:14:01.416 --> 00:14:03.916
That was a thousand times better
than I'd imagined.

199
00:14:06.791 --> 00:14:07.666
Hasley. sweetie.

200
00:14:09.625 --> 00:14:10.791
Mom. what's up?

201
00:14:12.166 --> 00:14:15.875
This is Matt. We go to school together.
He was walking me home.

202
00:14:15.958 --> 00:14:17.541
Mom. Matt. Matt. Mom.

203
00:14:17.625 --> 00:14:19.208
-Pleased to meet you.
-Likewise.

204
00:14:19.708 --> 00:14:21.375
Are you staying for dinner. Matt?

205
00:14:21.458 --> 00:14:24.833
I'd love to. but I have to get going.
I was just walking her home.

206
00:14:24.916 --> 00:14:26.875
Well. see you tomorrow. Has.

207
00:14:33.625 --> 00:14:34.958
He's handsome. isn't he?

208
00:14:36.583 --> 00:14:37.750
Mom. stop.

209
00:14:40.083 --> 00:14:41.541
Come on. last lap.

210
00:14:47.083 --> 00:14:49.791
What are you doing?
You're going to come last because of me.

211
00:14:50.500 --> 00:14:52.333
Relax. I'm fine here.

212
00:14:57.666 --> 00:14:59.416
Okay. we're done.

213
00:15:01.541 --> 00:15:03.041
Okay. everyone. go shower.

214
00:15:04.583 --> 00:15:07.333
Come on. bro. spill it. We want details.

215
00:15:08.833 --> 00:15:11.916
I'm not telling you anything.
You know I'm a gentleman.

216
00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:16.916
Yes. that's why you came last in the race.
to help Hasley. Right. "gentleman"?

217
00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.500
-Exactly.
-Bro. don't be like that. Tell us.

218
00:15:19.583 --> 00:15:23.541
You're not gonna tell us. are you. Romeo?
Come on. gentleman. He's in love.

219
00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:28.833
-What time do we have to be there?
-Any time after 6:00.

220
00:15:28.916 --> 00:15:31.375
-You can arrive whenever you want.
-Okay. Good time.

221
00:15:31.458 --> 00:15:32.833
Does she know about the party?

222
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.000
I'm at home alone.
if you want to come over.

223
00:15:36.083 --> 00:15:37.333
Okay. Thanks.

224
00:15:37.416 --> 00:15:40.666
Matt's coming too.
How was yesterday? Tell us.

225
00:15:41.875 --> 00:15:43.541
It was good.

226
00:15:43.625 --> 00:15:47.333
We went out for a drink and he insisted
I go to his basketball practice.

227
00:15:47.416 --> 00:15:49.083
They're obsessed with that.

228
00:15:49.166 --> 00:15:52.750
Yeah. Then he walked me home and…

229
00:15:54.375 --> 00:15:55.541
-And he kissed me.
-What?

230
00:15:55.625 --> 00:15:56.666
Yeah.

231
00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:58.916
-You don't waste time. do you?
-Neither does he.

232
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.875
You go. girl. You just say yes.

233
00:16:01.791 --> 00:16:03.875
I really want to party!

234
00:16:04.583 --> 00:16:07.166
-But now. I have Physics class.
-What a drag.

235
00:16:12.375 --> 00:16:13.291
Hi.

236
00:16:20.166 --> 00:16:22.500
Okay. Take your seats.

237
00:16:29.458 --> 00:16:32.083
What are you doing here?
Find another chair. go on.

238
00:16:32.166 --> 00:16:34.458
You're going to remind everyone I exist.

239
00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:38.208
Can you lower the blinds?

240
00:16:43.541 --> 00:16:46.750
Let's continue on the topic of optics.

241
00:16:47.791 --> 00:16:53.541
Light can bounce. just like a ball
that bounces off the ground.

242
00:16:53.625 --> 00:16:54.458
Luke.

243
00:16:55.125 --> 00:16:55.958
Weigel.

244
00:16:57.375 --> 00:16:58.583
What are you drawing?

245
00:17:00.625 --> 00:17:02.500
You're not wearing a stained shirt today.

246
00:17:05.541 --> 00:17:07.208
How old are you?

247
00:17:08.583 --> 00:17:09.833
Nineteen.

248
00:17:09.916 --> 00:17:11.458
Seriously?

249
00:17:11.541 --> 00:17:12.916
Be quiet. please.

250
00:17:14.208 --> 00:17:15.208
Thank you.

251
00:17:16.875 --> 00:17:19.041
That's why we see our reflection.

252
00:17:19.125 --> 00:17:22.250
Because the light comes back to us
with our image.

253
00:17:23.250 --> 00:17:25.000
Let's move to the next slide.

254
00:17:26.583 --> 00:17:28.000
Diffuse reflection.

255
00:17:28.791 --> 00:17:33.666
Light is reflected in multiple directions
due to irregularities in the surface.

256
00:17:36.333 --> 00:17:38.333
{\an8}GOSSIP

257
00:17:53.166 --> 00:17:54.083
Welcome.

258
00:17:54.916 --> 00:17:56.666
Your house is so beautiful.

259
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:59.875
Yeah right. It's not mine.
it's my parents'. I'm not that tacky.

260
00:17:59.958 --> 00:18:01.000
Have fun.

261
00:18:02.583 --> 00:18:04.416
Hey. bro!

262
00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:07.083
-I brought you a little gift. dude.
-You're late. bro.

263
00:18:07.166 --> 00:18:09.166
Come on. Let's drink.

264
00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:12.708
-Shit. Okay. okay.
-Come on!

265
00:18:15.083 --> 00:18:16.541
My goodness!

266
00:18:16.625 --> 00:18:18.958
Shut up. I still freeze when he does that.

267
00:18:19.041 --> 00:18:20.125
You'll get over it.

268
00:18:25.958 --> 00:18:27.333
What's going on here?

269
00:18:28.916 --> 00:18:31.041
-Hi!
-Sorry. I'm a little busy.

270
00:18:31.125 --> 00:18:33.083
-See you in a bit.
-No worries.

271
00:18:33.166 --> 00:18:36.958
-Did she invite half the school or what?
-Yeah. it sure looks like it.

272
00:18:39.500 --> 00:18:41.208
Where the hell does this thing go?

273
00:18:42.666 --> 00:18:44.750
-Put the music back on!
-Sorry.

274
00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:47.958
-Hi. Can I help?
-Please.

275
00:18:48.541 --> 00:18:49.791
My buddy left me here alone.

276
00:18:49.875 --> 00:18:51.791
I stepped on the cables
and messed things up.

277
00:18:51.875 --> 00:18:55.083
So you snuck in and you cut the music.
Do you think that's nice?

278
00:18:55.166 --> 00:18:57.500
Hey. my buddy goes to your school. okay?
And I. well…

279
00:18:58.791 --> 00:18:59.791
Well?

280
00:19:00.666 --> 00:19:02.416
-Hi.
-Hi.

281
00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:07.750
Look. this goes here…

282
00:19:09.208 --> 00:19:10.583
-Dude.
-What's wrong with you?

283
00:19:10.666 --> 00:19:13.958
-Can we talk?
-No. I have nothing to say to you.

284
00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:19.583
Look. and this one goes here.

285
00:19:20.916 --> 00:19:22.083
Done.

286
00:19:22.166 --> 00:19:25.125
Damn! You're pretty good at this.

287
00:19:25.208 --> 00:19:28.666
Yeah. I like DJing. so I have to know
about gadgets and cables.

288
00:19:29.541 --> 00:19:30.458
Right.

289
00:19:31.708 --> 00:19:32.625
I'm Olivia.

290
00:19:34.083 --> 00:19:35.000
André.

291
00:19:37.291 --> 00:19:38.208
And that's Hasley.

292
00:19:40.416 --> 00:19:43.583
Hello. You guys want something to drink?

293
00:19:43.666 --> 00:19:45.041
No. we're okay. right?

294
00:19:45.875 --> 00:19:47.458
Yeah. Great.

295
00:20:01.750 --> 00:20:02.875
Bro. Has is here.

296
00:20:03.875 --> 00:20:05.041
-Say something to her.
-Me?

297
00:20:05.125 --> 00:20:06.291
Yeah. Go on.

298
00:20:06.375 --> 00:20:07.500
Say something to her.

299
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:12.750
I'm Sorry. Are you okay? So sorry.

300
00:20:12.833 --> 00:20:14.916
-Wait. I'll clean you up a bit.
-Okay.

301
00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:16.916
-I'm really clumsy.
-It's fine.

302
00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:20.083
It's fine. I'll go to the bathroom. okay?

303
00:20:20.791 --> 00:20:21.708
Okay.

304
00:20:30.666 --> 00:20:32.416
Come on. There's another one upstairs.

305
00:20:46.791 --> 00:20:49.000
How do you know your way
around this house so well?

306
00:20:49.083 --> 00:20:50.375
It's like a maze.

307
00:20:51.708 --> 00:20:52.625
Intuition.

308
00:20:58.000 --> 00:21:01.708
There's the bathroom.
Maybe I can give you a hand.

309
00:21:09.291 --> 00:21:10.583
I need to go.

310
00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:12.708
Shall I come with you?

311
00:21:15.916 --> 00:21:18.333
Oh. no. There's a line here too.

312
00:21:21.041 --> 00:21:22.500
Luke. what are you doing here?

313
00:21:23.125 --> 00:21:24.916
Looking for a vacant bathroom.

314
00:21:26.166 --> 00:21:27.000
You guys?

315
00:21:27.958 --> 00:21:31.416
-Right. I won't be long.
-No worries.

316
00:21:46.958 --> 00:21:47.791
Matt!

317
00:21:48.416 --> 00:21:50.291
Matt help me with Zev. he's wasted.

318
00:21:54.625 --> 00:21:57.833
Matt. come on! If he pukes
on Carla's floor. she'll kill us.

319
00:21:58.458 --> 00:21:59.375
I'm coming.

320
00:22:09.708 --> 00:22:12.041
If you want my advice. don't do it.

321
00:22:17.458 --> 00:22:20.500
You know what?
I'm a bit fed up with your advice.

322
00:22:20.583 --> 00:22:21.833
You don't know me at all.

323
00:22:23.833 --> 00:22:24.958
That can be fixed.

324
00:22:31.291 --> 00:22:32.750
You'd better take off your shirt.

325
00:22:33.833 --> 00:22:34.750
Excuse me?

326
00:22:51.541 --> 00:22:52.458
Take it.

327
00:22:56.333 --> 00:22:57.250
Turn around.

328
00:23:20.791 --> 00:23:21.625
Thanks.

329
00:23:22.458 --> 00:23:24.791
But I don't want people
to get any funny ideas.

330
00:23:25.791 --> 00:23:26.833
Done.

331
00:23:36.458 --> 00:23:38.250
Why do you care what they think?

332
00:23:38.333 --> 00:23:40.708
We all end up
on a boulevard of broken dreams.

333
00:23:46.250 --> 00:23:47.416
We should go downstairs.

334
00:23:51.375 --> 00:23:53.791
I've taken my role as your musical guide
very seriously.

335
00:24:01.750 --> 00:24:06.833
"Green Day. The Doors. The Who."
So nothing from this century.

336
00:24:07.791 --> 00:24:09.125
I only listen to the classics.

337
00:24:13.083 --> 00:24:17.500
Well. maybe I'm the one
who needs to teach you a thing or two.

338
00:24:19.708 --> 00:24:20.708
Maybe.

339
00:24:22.125 --> 00:24:24.083
But you have to listen to that with me.

340
00:24:25.083 --> 00:24:26.125
Promise?

341
00:24:28.291 --> 00:24:29.208
Of course.

342
00:24:31.125 --> 00:24:33.208
I'm leaving. This party sucks.

343
00:24:36.041 --> 00:24:37.291
Where are you going?

344
00:24:37.916 --> 00:24:39.458
To a place you'd love.

345
00:24:54.166 --> 00:24:56.041
What a great song! Right?

346
00:24:57.500 --> 00:24:59.000
It doesn't ring a bell.

347
00:25:00.708 --> 00:25:01.541
Carla. I love you.

348
00:25:01.625 --> 00:25:04.166
-He's gonna puke in my living room.
-That's enough.

349
00:25:15.791 --> 00:25:18.833
Let's see if this place you're
talking about is really that wonderful.

350
00:25:21.666 --> 00:25:23.833
So. Weigel. do you trust me?

351
00:25:25.291 --> 00:25:26.208
No.

352
00:25:28.125 --> 00:25:29.041
Excellent.

353
00:26:09.916 --> 00:26:10.833
Wait.

354
00:26:26.166 --> 00:26:27.125
What is this place?

355
00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:29.916
It's a secret.

356
00:26:40.083 --> 00:26:40.916
Close your eyes.

357
00:26:42.708 --> 00:26:44.250
It's fine. Close your eyes.

358
00:26:49.083 --> 00:26:49.916
Come on.

359
00:26:53.541 --> 00:26:54.458
Careful.

360
00:26:57.333 --> 00:26:58.250
This way.

361
00:27:04.916 --> 00:27:05.833
Stop.

362
00:27:19.625 --> 00:27:20.958
Open your eyes.

363
00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:28.166
Welcome to the boulevard of broken dreams.

364
00:28:17.750 --> 00:28:18.625
It's beautiful.

365
00:28:21.750 --> 00:28:23.458
I found it with my brother. Zach.

366
00:28:25.916 --> 00:28:28.083
Look. when there's a full moon.

367
00:28:28.166 --> 00:28:31.583
the light shines through that crystal
and a rainbow appears.

368
00:28:34.416 --> 00:28:36.791
The last few days.
I've been wanting to show it to you.

369
00:28:37.916 --> 00:28:38.958
Do you like it?

370
00:28:39.833 --> 00:28:40.750
Yeah.

371
00:28:54.916 --> 00:28:56.208
{\an8}This was Zach's.

372
00:28:59.250 --> 00:29:02.291
{\an8}I'm sure your friends told you by now.

373
00:29:03.750 --> 00:29:06.708
My dad went nuts one day
and wanted to throw it all away.

374
00:29:06.791 --> 00:29:08.541
We fought and I brought it here.

375
00:29:14.666 --> 00:29:17.416
{\an8}-Are those yours?
-Yeah. they're my favorites.

376
00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:19.875
I keep the rest at home.

377
00:29:19.958 --> 00:29:21.958
My brother Pol brings me some from London.

378
00:29:22.041 --> 00:29:23.541
How many do you have?

379
00:29:23.625 --> 00:29:28.083
-I don't know. around 500.
-Exactly 500 or more?

380
00:29:28.708 --> 00:29:29.708
Does that matter?

381
00:29:29.791 --> 00:29:32.208
It does. You have to count them for me.

382
00:29:34.041 --> 00:29:34.958
Seriously?

383
00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:37.083
Very seriously.

384
00:29:44.583 --> 00:29:50.541
Hey. that thing about the boulevard
of broken dreams you mentioned before…

385
00:29:51.541 --> 00:29:52.708
What's that all about?

386
00:29:53.875 --> 00:29:56.333
Such a lovely place
shouldn't have that name.

387
00:29:57.833 --> 00:29:59.708
It's the title
of one of my favorite songs.

388
00:30:00.666 --> 00:30:03.041
When a dream is shattered.
it ends up on the boulevard.

389
00:30:03.875 --> 00:30:04.791
I don't understand.

390
00:30:09.958 --> 00:30:11.958
You will.
when one of your dreams shatters.

391
00:30:13.041 --> 00:30:16.291
Well. you've seen my list.
Most of them remain unfulfilled.

392
00:30:16.958 --> 00:30:19.708
Why have them
if you don't try to fulfill them?

393
00:30:20.416 --> 00:30:22.375
Says the guy who claims to have no dreams.

394
00:30:46.791 --> 00:30:51.625
I started the list when I realized my mom
was never going to settle in one place.

395
00:30:52.333 --> 00:30:53.291
Because of her work?

396
00:30:54.041 --> 00:30:57.541
No. I think she's afraid of settling down
and reliving what happened with my dad.

397
00:30:59.083 --> 00:31:02.625
He left when I was two.
and we never saw him again.

398
00:31:05.375 --> 00:31:06.750
I got my odd surname from him.

399
00:31:06.833 --> 00:31:09.708
and an obsession with jotting down stuff
that I'll never do.

400
00:31:19.916 --> 00:31:22.958
You know what? I liked your idea.

401
00:31:43.250 --> 00:31:45.500
I'll make my own list of dreams.
and you'll help me.

402
00:31:45.583 --> 00:31:48.291
-To write it down?
-No. silly. to fulfill them.

403
00:31:48.375 --> 00:31:49.833
And I'll help you fulfill yours.

404
00:32:02.416 --> 00:32:07.500
DRIVE
WITH NO DESTINATION

405
00:32:10.208 --> 00:32:11.666
"Drive with no destination."

406
00:32:16.125 --> 00:32:17.125
Okay.

407
00:32:17.208 --> 00:32:18.291
But first…

408
00:32:22.291 --> 00:32:23.125
I can't dance.

409
00:32:23.208 --> 00:32:24.375
Me neither.

410
00:33:21.166 --> 00:33:22.416
Come on. I'll take you home.

411
00:33:25.750 --> 00:33:26.666
Luke.

412
00:33:45.541 --> 00:33:47.041
MATT
Are you home?

413
00:33:50.541 --> 00:33:52.333
Yes. about to get into bed

414
00:34:01.625 --> 00:34:04.208
-You really don't like it? It's the best.
-No. girl.

415
00:34:05.291 --> 00:34:07.625
-Come on. we'll be late.
-What time is it?

416
00:34:07.708 --> 00:34:09.041
-Hi.
-How are you?

417
00:34:09.125 --> 00:34:10.125
Good. Hi.

418
00:34:10.208 --> 00:34:11.708
-What's up?
-Let's go.

419
00:34:11.791 --> 00:34:12.958
Come on. Let's go inside.

420
00:34:14.041 --> 00:34:15.291
Luke Howland. dude.

421
00:34:18.083 --> 00:34:21.250
Can we have seven tickets for <i>Silence?</i>

422
00:34:21.333 --> 00:34:23.708
Too bad. It's full.

423
00:34:24.458 --> 00:34:25.541
It can't be.

424
00:34:25.625 --> 00:34:27.541
There are plenty of tickets
available online.

425
00:34:30.375 --> 00:34:31.291
What's up. Weigel?

426
00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:34.333
We could watch another one.

427
00:34:34.416 --> 00:34:36.333
-Yeah.
-No. <i>Silence.</i>

428
00:34:38.875 --> 00:34:40.333
We came to watch <i>Silence.</i>

429
00:34:40.416 --> 00:34:41.666
If you didn't…

430
00:34:41.750 --> 00:34:45.333
Shit. Sorry. man. it was an accident.

431
00:34:50.791 --> 00:34:51.958
Hey. what's wrong?

432
00:34:58.791 --> 00:35:01.541
Luke. get back here!

433
00:35:01.625 --> 00:35:03.708
Looks like your son doesn't like to work.

434
00:35:05.791 --> 00:35:07.708
Matt. forget it. please.

435
00:35:07.791 --> 00:35:09.458
I told you. He's dangerous.

436
00:35:26.291 --> 00:35:27.458
What's up. man?

437
00:35:28.500 --> 00:35:30.791
-Aren't you working today?
-Hey. Pushi!

438
00:35:30.875 --> 00:35:33.458
Stop it. I told you not to call me that.

439
00:35:33.541 --> 00:35:35.500
My little cousin is in a bad mood today.

440
00:35:37.791 --> 00:35:39.166
Are you looking for this?

441
00:35:45.125 --> 00:35:46.958
No. I'll pass. I'm opening tomorrow.

442
00:35:47.041 --> 00:35:49.625
Have you spoken to Olivia or Hasley?

443
00:35:49.708 --> 00:35:52.208
I don't hang out with those people. okay?

444
00:35:52.291 --> 00:35:53.500
Don't get your hopes up.

445
00:35:53.583 --> 00:35:56.416
I'm not getting my hopes up.
I felt a connection. We talked loads!

446
00:35:56.500 --> 00:35:57.875
-"Loads"?
-Yeah.

447
00:35:58.666 --> 00:35:59.666
Loads.

448
00:36:00.208 --> 00:36:03.958
Listen. stop fooling around
and open your mouth. okay?

449
00:36:46.541 --> 00:36:52.583
When light passes through a raindrop.
each color disperses and forms a rainbow.

450
00:36:52.666 --> 00:36:57.375
So next time you see a rainbow.
you'll know you're seeing pure physics.

451
00:36:57.458 --> 00:36:58.708
We'll continue tomorrow.

452
00:37:01.708 --> 00:37:03.375
-What's up?
-Hi.

453
00:37:04.458 --> 00:37:06.041
Want to do something this afternoon?

454
00:37:06.625 --> 00:37:07.875
What do you have in mind?

455
00:37:08.875 --> 00:37:11.625
I can pick you up after practice
and we'll go somewhere?

456
00:37:12.708 --> 00:37:14.416
-Okay.
-Perfect.

457
00:37:15.041 --> 00:37:17.208
Bro. come on. let's go.

458
00:37:17.291 --> 00:37:18.458
I'm coming.

459
00:37:18.541 --> 00:37:21.250
Get dressed up. okay? I'll text you later.

460
00:37:22.291 --> 00:37:23.291
What's up?

461
00:37:23.375 --> 00:37:25.541
We've got practice.
Let's go. we're gonna be late.

462
00:38:04.916 --> 00:38:09.041
Hey. Matt. everything will be closed
by the time you get here.

463
00:38:31.041 --> 00:38:32.208
Five hundred and three.

464
00:38:40.208 --> 00:38:41.500
What?

465
00:38:41.583 --> 00:38:43.375
My vinyl records. I have 503.

466
00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:57.083
Strawberry ice cream.

467
00:38:59.708 --> 00:39:01.000
And popcorn?

468
00:39:01.750 --> 00:39:03.291
What? It's the perfect combination.

469
00:39:04.125 --> 00:39:05.458
I really like it.

470
00:39:07.500 --> 00:39:08.625
Now I do too.

471
00:39:14.083 --> 00:39:15.333
What are you doing here?

472
00:39:17.666 --> 00:39:19.000
I can't believe it.

473
00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:21.666
I didn't even notice…

474
00:39:22.958 --> 00:39:23.958
Sorry.

475
00:39:25.625 --> 00:39:28.333
{\an8}MATT
Rain check. I'm dead tired

476
00:39:35.541 --> 00:39:36.666
Want to go for a ride?

477
00:39:44.125 --> 00:39:45.041
Don't do that.

478
00:39:46.708 --> 00:39:48.375
I love the way you hold on to me.

479
00:40:04.250 --> 00:40:05.416
So. 503. huh?

480
00:40:07.916 --> 00:40:09.291
Not one more. not one less.

481
00:40:10.583 --> 00:40:11.791
Why so curious?

482
00:40:12.916 --> 00:40:15.041
I wanted to see if you'd reach 520.

483
00:40:15.708 --> 00:40:16.875
That's pretty specific.

484
00:40:19.833 --> 00:40:21.666
I know it's dumb. but…

485
00:40:22.875 --> 00:40:25.375
in China. the number 520…

486
00:40:26.666 --> 00:40:28.250
means "I love you."

487
00:40:30.208 --> 00:40:34.541
I've always wanted to get 520 roses
to remind myself that I love myself…

488
00:40:35.708 --> 00:40:37.083
and that I am enough.

489
00:40:41.333 --> 00:40:42.291
I like that.

490
00:40:54.250 --> 00:40:55.375
Why do you smoke that?

491
00:40:58.166 --> 00:40:59.083
It makes me fly.

492
00:41:07.916 --> 00:41:09.083
Let me try.

493
00:41:09.166 --> 00:41:11.625
You don't mind putting a joint
in your mouth now. Weigel?

494
00:41:13.375 --> 00:41:14.666
Will you let me or not?

495
00:41:20.416 --> 00:41:21.333
No.

496
00:41:52.333 --> 00:41:54.750
I hope you're ready for the journey
through good music.

497
00:42:18.041 --> 00:42:19.583
Hey. we're already closed. okay?

498
00:42:19.666 --> 00:42:23.000
But I have work to do in the back room.
so the store is all yours.

499
00:42:23.083 --> 00:42:24.458
Perfect. man. Thanks.

500
00:42:39.250 --> 00:42:41.333
You must love this place. right?

501
00:42:41.416 --> 00:42:42.833
Music is my refuge.

502
00:43:04.291 --> 00:43:05.208
Are you ready?

503
00:45:04.041 --> 00:45:05.666
If I don't do it now. I'll regret it.

504
00:46:11.250 --> 00:46:13.916
-Hey. Pol.
<i>-Luke. What's up? Are you okay?</i>

505
00:46:14.666 --> 00:46:17.041
Why do you ask?
Can't I call my older brother?

506
00:46:18.291 --> 00:46:20.083
<i>This late? You?</i>

507
00:46:20.166 --> 00:46:21.708
You're one hour behind there.

508
00:46:23.250 --> 00:46:25.333
<i>Seriously. what's wrong?</i>

509
00:46:27.166 --> 00:46:30.333
I'm starting to remember
what it's like to be happy. brother.

510
00:46:31.375 --> 00:46:33.125
<i>You have to start from the beginning.</i>

511
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:36.958
Well. let me tell you. I met a girl.

512
00:46:38.083 --> 00:46:39.625
Her name's Hasley.

513
00:46:42.166 --> 00:46:43.000
This one?

514
00:46:44.208 --> 00:46:45.125
No.

515
00:46:45.958 --> 00:46:47.041
Okay.

516
00:46:52.541 --> 00:46:55.583
What are you supposed to wear
to your first DJ gig?

517
00:46:56.458 --> 00:46:58.166
Yeah. It's a big deal. isn't it?

518
00:46:58.250 --> 00:47:01.250
A really big deal.
I wouldn't have bet on André.

519
00:47:01.333 --> 00:47:02.416
He's done well.

520
00:47:03.583 --> 00:47:04.416
Oli…

521
00:47:06.291 --> 00:47:07.625
how would you make a playlist?

522
00:47:08.375 --> 00:47:12.166
I think it's important
that it tells a story.

523
00:47:13.083 --> 00:47:16.125
And then. make sure the songs
mean something to you.

524
00:47:16.208 --> 00:47:17.500
Or to Luke.

525
00:47:21.041 --> 00:47:24.083
No. guys. It's not what you think.

526
00:47:24.166 --> 00:47:26.666
No. we're not thinking about anything.

527
00:47:26.750 --> 00:47:27.666
No.

528
00:47:27.750 --> 00:47:31.625
I saw you two leave Carla's party together
and you're always looking at each other.

529
00:47:32.583 --> 00:47:34.958
You could cut the tension
between you two with a knife.

530
00:47:36.375 --> 00:47:37.458
I'm gonna try this on.

531
00:47:38.208 --> 00:47:40.541
Yeah. but I don't know
what's going on with me.

532
00:47:40.625 --> 00:47:41.666
I'm so confused.

533
00:47:41.750 --> 00:47:45.125
And I know this is wrong.
and I know Luke isn't good for me and…

534
00:47:46.041 --> 00:47:49.583
-I'm really lucky that Matt likes me…
-What? No. no. no.

535
00:47:49.666 --> 00:47:52.291
Matt's the one who's lucky to be with you.

536
00:47:52.375 --> 00:47:53.500
Not the other way around.

537
00:47:53.583 --> 00:47:56.625
I mean. it's true that Luke
isn't an easy guy to deal with.

538
00:47:56.708 --> 00:47:59.166
especially after his brother's accident.

539
00:47:59.250 --> 00:48:01.166
You should know what you're getting into.

540
00:48:02.291 --> 00:48:03.583
I think I know.

541
00:48:03.666 --> 00:48:06.333
We're telling you this
because we care about you.

542
00:48:06.416 --> 00:48:09.208
And we also care about him.
He used to hang out with us before.

543
00:48:09.291 --> 00:48:10.541
Really?

544
00:48:11.458 --> 00:48:13.458
Even though it seems impossible now.

545
00:48:13.541 --> 00:48:16.375
the first person I told that I liked boys
was Luke.

546
00:48:17.125 --> 00:48:22.333
But then the accident happened
and he changed.

547
00:48:22.416 --> 00:48:27.375
He started going all out on drugs
and had some sort of run-in with Matt.

548
00:48:27.458 --> 00:48:28.583
and that was that.

549
00:48:29.708 --> 00:48:31.791
-It was shitty.
-I had no idea.

550
00:48:32.625 --> 00:48:34.291
That's why you should be careful.

551
00:48:34.375 --> 00:48:36.625
And make a choice
before you go any further.

552
00:48:40.125 --> 00:48:41.166
This is the one.

553
00:48:41.916 --> 00:48:43.041
You look incredible.

554
00:48:43.125 --> 00:48:44.208
This is the one.

555
00:48:49.250 --> 00:48:50.166
Has.

556
00:48:52.375 --> 00:48:53.291
Has.

557
00:48:57.375 --> 00:48:58.250
Hasley.

558
00:48:58.916 --> 00:49:00.791
I'm sorry. I lost track of time and…

559
00:49:00.875 --> 00:49:02.125
Practice.

560
00:49:02.208 --> 00:49:05.125
What did you do?
Did you miss me? A little. right?

561
00:49:12.833 --> 00:49:14.250
Let's get to class.

562
00:49:15.916 --> 00:49:17.500
Hi. good morning.

563
00:49:32.625 --> 00:49:33.458
Luke.

564
00:49:34.666 --> 00:49:35.583
It's not that easy.

565
00:49:37.833 --> 00:49:38.833
Silence.

566
00:49:44.916 --> 00:49:48.250
Hey. what happened between us
was great. but…

567
00:49:48.333 --> 00:49:49.333
But you're with Matt.

568
00:49:49.916 --> 00:49:51.708
I'm going to dump him.

569
00:49:51.791 --> 00:49:54.000
I just need to find
the right time to do it.

570
00:50:14.458 --> 00:50:15.583
Do you trust me?

571
00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:28.416
Weigel.

572
00:50:30.416 --> 00:50:32.416
-What?
-Am I a good kisser?

573
00:50:34.000 --> 00:50:35.041
Too much tongue.

574
00:50:49.208 --> 00:50:50.500
Do you think he'll let me?

575
00:50:51.916 --> 00:50:54.291
If you don't try.
you'll never know. cousin.

576
00:50:56.916 --> 00:50:57.833
I don't know.

577
00:51:01.875 --> 00:51:03.208
Go on. I'll finish up here.

578
00:51:05.625 --> 00:51:06.458
Go.

579
00:51:09.958 --> 00:51:12.375
Go on. Pushi. Come on.

580
00:51:15.750 --> 00:51:16.708
Cousin.

581
00:51:17.958 --> 00:51:19.208
I like seeing you like this.

582
00:51:23.875 --> 00:51:27.583
{\an8}SCREEN 1

583
00:51:30.250 --> 00:51:31.083
Dad.

584
00:51:31.708 --> 00:51:32.541
What?

585
00:51:32.625 --> 00:51:33.958
I need to ask you a favor.

586
00:51:35.583 --> 00:51:37.916
I want to stay here tonight
after the last screening.

587
00:51:39.791 --> 00:51:41.541
To prepare a surprise.

588
00:51:41.625 --> 00:51:44.708
You. a surprise? For who?

589
00:51:44.791 --> 00:51:45.958
A girl from class.

590
00:51:46.666 --> 00:51:49.000
Don't you realize
that you're not okay. son?

591
00:51:50.541 --> 00:51:54.000
Don't you realize
that if you really cared about this girl.

592
00:51:54.083 --> 00:51:56.958
the decent thing to do would be
to not get involved with her?

593
00:51:59.375 --> 00:52:00.750
You have no fucking clue.

594
00:52:00.833 --> 00:52:04.416
The one who doesn't have a freaking clue
about anything is you. son.

595
00:52:04.500 --> 00:52:10.375
You come home
high as a kite night after night.

596
00:52:10.458 --> 00:52:14.250
Do you know how worried your mother gets
every time you go out?

597
00:52:14.333 --> 00:52:20.000
What can you offer someone other than
problems. anguish. disappointment?

598
00:52:21.208 --> 00:52:22.125
You're an asshole.

599
00:52:36.375 --> 00:52:37.458
What are you doing here?

600
00:52:38.041 --> 00:52:39.500
I said I'd make it up to you.

601
00:52:40.083 --> 00:52:41.208
Do you forgive me?

602
00:52:44.708 --> 00:52:46.875
Matt. I don't think this is working.

603
00:52:46.958 --> 00:52:50.291
Has. I screwed up. okay? I know that. but…

604
00:52:50.375 --> 00:52:53.416
No. it's not that. Seriously.

605
00:52:53.500 --> 00:52:54.500
Yes. it is.

606
00:52:55.875 --> 00:52:57.041
And you're right. but…

607
00:52:57.958 --> 00:53:00.208
you're also tired. Okay?

608
00:53:00.958 --> 00:53:04.625
I'm going to a tournament on Friday.
We'll talk when I get back. okay?

609
00:53:10.000 --> 00:53:12.250
I have to go.
The coach is going to kill me.

610
00:53:17.541 --> 00:53:18.625
Bye.

611
00:55:48.583 --> 00:55:49.666
Get out of here! Go!

612
00:55:55.041 --> 00:55:57.375
That fucking does it!
What the hell's wrong with you?

613
00:55:57.458 --> 00:55:59.750
-Get lost. man!
-Luke. don't fuck with me.

614
00:55:59.833 --> 00:56:02.416
Get lost if you don't want me
to fuck up your life too!

615
00:56:03.083 --> 00:56:05.750
What are you saying?
I've been by your side my whole life!

616
00:56:05.833 --> 00:56:08.125
I won't bail out on you
even if you yell at me!

617
00:56:08.208 --> 00:56:11.333
You hear me?
You can't run away your whole life!

618
00:56:20.958 --> 00:56:22.208
-Look how pretty.
-I like it.

619
00:56:22.291 --> 00:56:23.333
{\an8}GLITTER PARTY
DECEMBER 5

620
00:56:23.416 --> 00:56:26.333
{\an8}We'd better do it properly
so we can raise cash for the trip.

621
00:56:26.416 --> 00:56:27.625
{\an8}-Yeah. girl.
-Yeah.

622
00:56:27.708 --> 00:56:30.333
{\an8}-Hasley. what do you think?
-Look.

623
00:56:30.416 --> 00:56:31.416
Let's see.

624
00:56:33.458 --> 00:56:34.375
Shall we get to it?

625
00:56:35.083 --> 00:56:38.000
It's nice. Where is it taking place?

626
00:56:38.083 --> 00:56:41.083
Here. like every year. Where else?

627
00:56:41.166 --> 00:56:42.916
She's new. She wouldn't know.

628
00:56:43.000 --> 00:56:45.208
Yet look how quickly
the girl's made an impression.

629
00:56:47.916 --> 00:56:49.291
Do you have a problem with me?

630
00:56:49.375 --> 00:56:51.750
Who. me? No. Why?

631
00:56:51.833 --> 00:56:54.875
Okay. let's all calm down.
Listen. Carla. don't worry.

632
00:56:54.958 --> 00:56:58.041
I'll take care of the music.
Let me know when the tickets are ready.

633
00:56:58.125 --> 00:57:00.458
-Perfect.
-Neizan and I will handle the catering…

634
00:57:07.500 --> 00:57:08.791
Mom. what…

635
00:57:23.333 --> 00:57:24.541
I'm sorry. I didn't…

636
00:57:24.625 --> 00:57:27.125
You should have knocked. Hasley.

637
00:57:55.083 --> 00:57:56.458
Sorry about earlier.

638
00:57:57.666 --> 00:58:00.541
I shouldn't have barged in.
I didn't know you were seeing my mom.

639
00:58:01.750 --> 00:58:03.166
Go away. Please.

640
00:58:17.375 --> 00:58:19.041
I'm not going to leave you here alone.

641
00:58:30.250 --> 00:58:31.625
Go away I said.

642
00:58:31.708 --> 00:58:35.166
Can't you see I'm bad for you.
that I'm going to screw up your life?

643
00:58:35.250 --> 00:58:37.000
I think I can decide that myself.

644
00:58:37.750 --> 00:58:39.583
The closer you get.
the more I'll hurt you.

645
00:58:44.083 --> 00:58:45.833
You're scared. Luke.

646
00:58:48.083 --> 00:58:49.208
And I'm scared too.

647
00:58:51.083 --> 00:58:52.708
I don't know what's going on with me.

648
00:58:54.500 --> 00:58:56.750
What I do know is
I can't walk away from this.

649
00:58:58.208 --> 00:59:01.583
Weigel. you have a perfect life
with a perfect boyfriend. and I…

650
00:59:01.666 --> 00:59:03.000
My perfect boyfriend.

651
00:59:04.125 --> 00:59:06.041
I want to break up with him. Luke.

652
00:59:08.833 --> 00:59:11.291
I saw you two yesterday. at your house.

653
00:59:17.500 --> 00:59:21.375
I don't care what you think you saw
or what other people think.

654
00:59:23.041 --> 00:59:24.791
Matt isn't for me.

655
00:59:31.791 --> 00:59:37.083
Luke. if you want me to leave.
you'll have to push me away yourself.

656
00:59:48.000 --> 00:59:48.833
See?

657
00:59:50.541 --> 00:59:51.791
You can't do it either.

658
01:00:16.625 --> 01:00:17.458
What's this?

659
01:00:18.916 --> 01:00:19.916
I did my homework.

660
01:00:23.416 --> 01:00:27.875
"Surprise someone.
Jump off a cliff into the sea."

661
01:00:28.666 --> 01:00:29.958
"Travel to Amsterdam."

662
01:00:31.375 --> 01:00:33.875
"Sing without caring who's watching me."

663
01:00:37.208 --> 01:00:38.250
This is really good.

664
01:00:42.416 --> 01:00:43.958
You know what?

665
01:00:44.041 --> 01:00:46.958
I'm not leaving here today
without seeing the moon's reflection.

666
01:00:48.541 --> 01:00:49.541
Can I refuse?

667
01:00:51.500 --> 01:00:52.833
I don't think you want to.

668
01:00:54.500 --> 01:00:55.416
Maybe not.

669
01:00:59.000 --> 01:00:59.916
Thanks.

670
01:01:01.750 --> 01:01:04.000
-For what?
-For not leaving me here alone.

671
01:01:17.333 --> 01:01:20.333
LIGHT FIREWORKS

672
01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:50.500
PLANT A TREE

673
01:02:07.083 --> 01:02:09.000
TRAVEL TO PARIS

674
01:03:22.500 --> 01:03:24.500
SLEEP UNDER THE STARS

675
01:04:25.458 --> 01:04:29.375
Since I can't fulfill your dream
and take you to swim with dolphins…

676
01:04:30.916 --> 01:04:31.833
It's perfect.

677
01:04:43.625 --> 01:04:44.666
What's this?

678
01:04:45.583 --> 01:04:48.458
My interpretation of life.
a roulette wheel.

679
01:04:48.541 --> 01:04:52.166
Sometimes you win. sometimes you lose.
It's cruel and fair. in its own way.

680
01:04:53.875 --> 01:04:57.583
No. I think of life more like…

681
01:04:59.791 --> 01:05:01.958
like a story we're improvising.

682
01:05:02.041 --> 01:05:04.750
And it's full of mistakes and stuff. but…

683
01:05:05.708 --> 01:05:08.166
I don't know.
you keep reading because you're hooked

684
01:05:08.250 --> 01:05:11.125
and you want to know
what happens in the next chapter.

685
01:05:11.208 --> 01:05:13.750
Damn. Weigel. You're such a romantic.

686
01:05:16.208 --> 01:05:18.916
And you're a gambling addict.
Give me a break.

687
01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:22.458
Well. this is starting
to feel like an addiction.

688
01:05:26.458 --> 01:05:27.458
Luke.

689
01:05:29.583 --> 01:05:33.250
I want to do things right.
I want us to stop hiding.

690
01:05:34.916 --> 01:05:38.375
We're destroying ourselves
in the most beautiful way possible.

691
01:05:38.458 --> 01:05:39.541
Don't you see that?

692
01:05:41.166 --> 01:05:46.291
We're creating our own boulevard.
And whatever happens. I won't regret it.

693
01:06:10.625 --> 01:06:12.333
-Go on. Good!
-Very good.

694
01:06:13.208 --> 01:06:14.333
Shit.

695
01:06:14.916 --> 01:06:16.041
Very good. kid.

696
01:06:25.291 --> 01:06:26.291
Matt.

697
01:06:27.708 --> 01:06:28.916
Can we talk?

698
01:06:29.833 --> 01:06:32.583
Why so serious? What's wrong. baby?

699
01:06:33.333 --> 01:06:36.000
Well. I meant in private.

700
01:06:36.083 --> 01:06:37.208
Sure. in a minute.

701
01:06:38.041 --> 01:06:40.000
Matt. just go. We're not doing anything.

702
01:06:42.541 --> 01:06:46.875
Look. I'll go when I feel like it.
Are you telling me what I have to do now?

703
01:06:46.958 --> 01:06:49.666
He's not telling you anything.
I'm asking you.

704
01:06:54.916 --> 01:06:55.833
Are you okay?

705
01:06:57.791 --> 01:06:59.041
Well…

706
01:07:00.458 --> 01:07:02.375
Come on. Tell me.

707
01:07:04.958 --> 01:07:05.958
Okay.

708
01:07:07.083 --> 01:07:09.125
Look. I've been thinking and…

709
01:07:10.875 --> 01:07:12.458
I don't think this is working.

710
01:07:13.833 --> 01:07:14.958
What's not working?

711
01:07:16.833 --> 01:07:18.166
Us. Matt.

712
01:07:18.875 --> 01:07:21.083
I tried to make it work. but…

713
01:07:21.166 --> 01:07:22.541
Enough already. Has.

714
01:07:22.625 --> 01:07:26.125
I get that you're overwhelmed
with school and everything.

715
01:07:26.208 --> 01:07:27.791
but I think you're being hasty.

716
01:07:27.875 --> 01:07:28.750
I'm sure about this.

717
01:07:28.833 --> 01:07:31.458
No. Has. You're not sure.

718
01:07:32.750 --> 01:07:35.500
Do you need space? I can wait.

719
01:07:36.666 --> 01:07:38.916
It'll be good for us
to take a break for a few days.

720
01:07:39.666 --> 01:07:40.791
Come on!

721
01:07:42.291 --> 01:07:44.625
Matt. the coach is calling us. Come on.

722
01:07:44.708 --> 01:07:45.958
Bro. move it. let's go.

723
01:07:46.541 --> 01:07:49.125
I'm stopping you from making
the worst mistake of your life.

724
01:07:56.166 --> 01:07:58.000
You're stunning. You look like a star.

725
01:07:58.083 --> 01:08:00.250
Have you seen yourself?
That dress is gorgeous.

726
01:08:01.208 --> 01:08:02.291
Listen.

727
01:08:02.375 --> 01:08:03.583
What?

728
01:08:03.666 --> 01:08:04.625
I love you.

729
01:08:04.708 --> 01:08:08.291
I love you too! Okay. ready? Let's go.

730
01:08:10.833 --> 01:08:12.208
Here we go.

731
01:08:16.041 --> 01:08:17.416
You're so beautiful.

732
01:08:17.500 --> 01:08:19.750
-Hi.
-Hi.

733
01:08:19.833 --> 01:08:20.750
Hi.

734
01:08:42.208 --> 01:08:44.333
I thought you were gonna chicken out.

735
01:08:44.416 --> 01:08:46.208
I want to get to know your world.

736
01:08:46.291 --> 01:08:48.541
This isn't my world.
it's just where I hide.

737
01:08:49.333 --> 01:08:52.208
We have a very special person
with us today.

738
01:08:52.291 --> 01:08:54.125
She's come to DJ for the first time.

739
01:08:54.208 --> 01:08:58.625
So let's give some love to Olivia!

740
01:09:01.291 --> 01:09:04.291
-Relax. you're gonna crush it. okay?
-Okay. Thanks.

741
01:09:04.375 --> 01:09:05.500
Come on. break a leg.

742
01:09:07.125 --> 01:09:08.041
Hey…

743
01:10:14.791 --> 01:10:16.375
-You were amazing.
-Yeah?

744
01:10:16.458 --> 01:10:18.458
It's like you've been doing it
your whole life.

745
01:10:18.541 --> 01:10:19.916
-Thanks.
-Let's go.

746
01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:21.125
Hey. love birds.

747
01:10:21.208 --> 01:10:22.416
Hi. I need to pee.

748
01:10:23.208 --> 01:10:24.500
That was incredible!

749
01:10:24.583 --> 01:10:28.041
Thanks! But I need to pee.
Would you come with me to the bathroom?

750
01:10:28.125 --> 01:10:29.041
Sure.

751
01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:30.916
Bye.

752
01:10:35.208 --> 01:10:36.291
Did you get it?

753
01:10:38.041 --> 01:10:39.083
What do you think?

754
01:10:41.166 --> 01:10:43.708
Of course. but it wasn't easy.

755
01:10:44.375 --> 01:10:45.625
Here.

756
01:10:47.791 --> 01:10:49.083
I owe you one.

757
01:10:49.166 --> 01:10:50.375
You owe me quite a few.

758
01:10:52.791 --> 01:10:53.791
Bastard.

759
01:11:07.375 --> 01:11:09.833
Well. I'm going that way.

760
01:11:10.625 --> 01:11:12.041
I'm going that way.

761
01:11:14.666 --> 01:11:15.833
I had a really good time.

762
01:11:15.916 --> 01:11:16.916
Me too.

763
01:11:18.333 --> 01:11:20.000
Now go dream. Weigel.

764
01:11:21.500 --> 01:11:23.041
I will. Howland.

765
01:12:01.500 --> 01:12:02.916
Weigel. would you like a ride?

766
01:12:04.500 --> 01:12:05.833
What's this?

767
01:12:06.791 --> 01:12:07.875
I'm fulfilling dreams.

768
01:12:09.125 --> 01:12:11.333
-Which one?
-I'm surprising someone.

769
01:12:23.375 --> 01:12:24.291
Where are we going?

770
01:12:26.291 --> 01:12:28.000
Let's just drive without a destination.

771
01:12:28.666 --> 01:12:29.583
Together?

772
01:12:30.375 --> 01:12:31.291
Together.

773
01:13:09.208 --> 01:13:10.583
The stars are so bright.

774
01:13:12.916 --> 01:13:14.333
